  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4444149219" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4444149219" />
    <a title="Valerria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/145486556-valerria"><img alt="Valerria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641283474p2/145486556.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4444149219?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Valerria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Valerria" href="/user/show/145486556-valerria">Valerria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4444149219" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3934905001482447767">Steve Pemberton compares our lives to that of a lighthouse, radiating light and hope to all we meet and cross in our everyday activities. He describes the presence of lighthouses, their roles, history, and position in society today. The accounts that ensue are examples of various ways of life. They are ordinary individuals with conflicts ( some more than others), who display remarkable “strength, conviction, courage and selflessness”. They all face their storms steadfastly, weathering their expe</span>
  <span id="freeText3934905001482447767" style="display:none">Steve Pemberton compares our lives to that of a lighthouse, radiating light and hope to all we meet and cross in our everyday activities. He describes the presence of lighthouses, their roles, history, and position in society today. The accounts that ensue are examples of various ways of life. They are ordinary individuals with conflicts ( some more than others), who display remarkable “strength, conviction, courage and selflessness”. They all face their storms steadfastly, weathering their experiences with their loved ones against the storm that rages around them, standing tall and proud. <br /><br />Unfortunately, we regularly undergo daily strife and hardship. But one random act, insignificant or useless as we may deem it, could encourage us to cope and even transform the world of another. Hence the lighthouse effect!<br /><br />The book begins. The initial passage I read is the meaningful quote by Gandalf from The Hobbit, one of my favourite movies. I immediately concluded this was going to be a great read! The author beautifully illustrates how we can act as a beacon in the stories of each other. Before you write this off, thinking, ‘I have nothing to give’…know this has nothing to do with wealth or possession. Found in the smallest of actions and, unknowingly, creates a monumental difference in the survival of an individual.<br /><br />“Your life experience is an opportunity to touch the life of another, to see in their life’s connection to your own”.<br /><br />The novel also includes advice and guidance on how to accomplish our goals by altering our strategy or even just our point of view, which is most helpful and makes total sense. We all have identified on getting out of bed each morning in a great mood how well that day continues for us. Even if something occurs during that time, we can either laugh it off or deal with it in a level-headed manner. Roll out of bed in a terrible mood, and things get worse as the day passes, affecting the attitude of everyone around us! If we establish the conscious judgment to treat everyone we meet with politeness and empathy, we feel better about ourselves. We could shine our light and improve the outlook of others! It’s all about the power of possibility, and it is possible!<br /><br />“Providing another with what you needed most is the path to healing yourself”.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3934905001482447767" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

